    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-02-23T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-02-23T19:00:00-05:00" n="405"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d405">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 405</seg>
                </opener>
                <note rend="inline" type="source">752.00/2–2351: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Spain</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d405fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_DWB1"
                            >Dunham</persName>, cleared and initialed over Secretary <persName
                            corresp="#p_ADG1">Acheson</persName>’s signature by <persName
                            corresp="#p_WFT1">Williamson</persName>, and repeated to London.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-02-23T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 23, 1951—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>539. Brit <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> states <gloss target="#t_FonOff1"
                        >FonOff</gloss> understands <persName corresp="#p_FYB1">Franco</persName>
                    may sound out US and UK Ambs re attitudes their govts if he “broadens base” his
                    regime. <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> thinks this maneuver connected
                        <persName corresp="#p_FYB1">Franco</persName>’s negots with Monarchists
                    since it is informed <persName corresp="#p_FYB1">Franco</persName> may meet soon
                    with Don <persName corresp="#p_JC1">Juan</persName>.<note n="2" xml:id="d405fn2"
                        >Pretender to the Spanish Throne.</note> Brit believes maneuver cld have two
                    purposes: 1) favor Monarchists over other opposition groups thus possibly
                    driving latter into hands Commies; 2) involve US and UK <gloss target="#t_Emb1"
                        >Emb</gloss>s in domestic Span polit intrigues.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> instructing Brit Amb, if approached,
                    give no indication type regime UK wld like see estab Spain and restrict his
                    remarks to saying simply Brit Govt wld like see Spain play its full role Western
                    Eur community but believes this will be difficult unless regime is
                    “liberalized”.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> instructed <gloss target="#t_Emb1"
                        >Emb</gloss> ask us instruct Amb <persName corresp="#p_GS1"
                        >Griffis</persName> similarly, in interest maintaining common policy re
                    Spain, informed <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> we had no info this subj but
                    wld inquire. Please advise.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ADG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
